<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🗿 Builder Basics — The Impossible Statue (Extension · Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Place + Move, On and Off · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 This is a bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it once you can place blocks and move the agent.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Read the World 🔍</h2>
<p>Open the <strong>Impossible Statue</strong> world. It is a puzzle. Look at the colours first:</p>
<ul>
<li>🟥 <strong>Red blocks</strong> — where the agent <strong>starts</strong> and where it <strong>ends</strong>.</li>
<li>⬛ <strong>Crying obsidian</strong> — <strong>build here</strong>. Place a block on every dark spot.</li>
<li>⬜ <strong>Glass</strong> — <strong>skip here</strong>. Move past it, but place <strong>nothing</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What do you do on a crying obsidian spot? Circle one:</strong> place a block · skip it</p>
<p><strong>What do you do on a glass spot? Circle one:</strong> place a block · skip it</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Place On, Place Off 💡</h2>
<p>On a build spot, you <strong>place</strong>. On a skip spot, you only <strong>move</strong> — no place.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
move forward
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks does this place? Circle one:</strong> 1 · 2 · 3</p>
<p><strong>Why do we skip a step? Circle one:</strong> it is a glass spot · it is a build spot · it is the start</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The pattern should be: <strong>build, skip, build</strong> (B S B). One line is missing.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
move forward
____________
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which line is missing? Circle one:</strong> move forward · place block down · turn right</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Find the Mistake 🐛</h2>
<p>The pattern should be <strong>build, skip, build</strong> (B S B). This code places a block on the skip spot by mistake.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
move forward
place block down
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> it builds on the skip spot · a build is missing · it turns the wrong way</p>
<hr />
<h2>5 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Go to the Impossible Statue world. Place blocks on the crying obsidian spots, skip the glass spots, and finish on the red end block.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
